            updated_at: '2022-10-13T04:37:35.216000Z',
            created_at: '2021-04-14T09:41:39.483000Z',
            description:
              '<p>The creases, ridges, or folds formed in the skin resulting in wrinkles. They begin to appear on your skin as you start to grow old. Wrinkles are fine lines that appear in areas where naturally the skin folds during facial expressions.&nbsp;</p><p>Wrinkles are a result when the skin starts to get thinner and less elastic with time. Wrinkles tend to develop in areas of the body, such as the face and neck, hands, and arms and are exposed to sunlight. Wrinkles naturally develop as you grow older and affect everybody.&nbsp;</p><h2>T<strong>reatment of wrinkles and fine lines&nbsp;</strong></h2><h3><strong>1.</strong>&nbsp; <strong>Medications for fine lines and wrinkles&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>Topical retinoids formulated from vitamin A. They help to reduce the appearance of fine lines, hyperpigmentation, and roughness of skin by increasing the production of collagen in the skin.</p><p>Applying retinoids in the sunlight can result in the burning of the skin. While applying the cream, it is important to protect the skin. The most negative effects can be:&nbsp;</p><p>\u00b7 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Burning sensation of skin</p><p>\u00b7 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Produces discoloration area in the skin</p><p>\u00b7 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Resulting in the skin to dry</p><p>\u00b7 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Itching of skin</p><h3><strong>2.</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Dermabrasion</strong></h3><p>A surgical procedure that is carried out by abrasion of the top layer of skin with the fast rotating device or controlled wearing away is called dermabrasion.&nbsp;</p><p>Dermabrasion aims at eliminating the appearance of thin wrinkles, moles, tattoos, acne scars, and other forms of scars. Scraping, swelling, and skin color changes can be the aftereffects of this procedure. These symptoms usually diminish after two weeks, while some signs can last for various months.</p><h3><strong>3.</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Botox</strong></h3><p>Type A Botulinum toxin or also known as Botox, restricts the chemical signals which lead to the contraction of muscles. Physicians are using it to treat some medical conditions, while a cosmetic surgeon can use it to eliminate the appearance of wrinkles with small doses of Botox injected into targeted muscles.&nbsp;</p><p>The skin flattens and gives a less wrinkling and cleaner look if the muscles cannot be tightened. Botox may reduce the appearance of lines on your forehead, the frown lines between the eyes, and the "crow\'s feet," which are around the corner of your eyes.&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>4.</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Fillers</strong></h3><p>Collagen, hyaluronic acid, or fat are part of the soft tissue fillers. A cosmetic surgeon will inject fillers in wrinkles of the face that appear deep; the fillers will smooth and plump to add more volume to the skin.</p><h2><strong>Tips to prevent fine lines and wrinkles</strong></h2><p>The appearance of fine lines and wrinkles gets more prominent as an individual starts to grow older. Some ways of preventing or reducing the appearance of fine lines or wrinkles include:&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Sun protection</strong></h3><p>By avoiding exposure to harmful UV radiation, the chances of skin damage are reduced. It is recommended by dermatologists to apply sunscreen formulated with SPF 30 or more along with wearing hats or clothing that protect you from harmful rays of the sun every day.</p><h3><strong>Moisturize regularly for fine lines&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>Dryness can be prevented by moisturizing your skin. Moisturizing your skin regularly reduces the chances of developing wrinkles.</p><h3><strong>Anti-wrinkle creams</strong></h3><p>Add the anti-wrinkle cream to your daily skincare routine. It gives you a radiant and young look. You should choose the best wrinkle cream according to your skin type.</p><h3><strong>Best eye creams for wrinkles</strong></h3><p>If you have wrinkles around the eyes, then you should use eye cream for wrinkles in your morning and night skincare routine.</p><h3><strong>Quit smoking</strong></h3><p>Smoking can greatly accelerate the aging of the skin and can promote the formation of wrinkles.&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Drink less alcohol</strong></h3><p>Consumption of alcohol can dehydrate the skin, causing long-term harm.</p><h3><strong>Balanced diet</strong></h3><p>Adding fruits and vegetables to your diet can prevent your skin from damage, while sugar and refined carbohydrates can accelerate the process of skin aging.</p><h3><strong>Facial cleanser two times a day</strong></h3><p>Add a gentle cleanser to your skincare routine. Rubbing your skin can result in irritation and accelerate the process of skin aging.</p><h3><strong>Wash the face after sweating</strong></h3><p>Sweat can result in irritation of the skin, causing damage gradually. This can greatly impact people wearing a hat or helmet.</p>',
